extra.remarks:
I marked "would" as F as I think it's meaning is more passive as when it is normally used as D.
I marked "have" as S conveying that "they" (the house managers) are responsible for the presence of the people at the pool. However, another possibility is to mark "down" as the state, denoting the relative location of the people (ex: the cup is on_S the table).
check as in bank deposit (alternative spelling: cheque)
